The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for improving the security of mobile crowdsensing systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of stacked autoencoder (SAE), deep neural network (DNN), and convolutional neural network (CNN), which are all machine learning techniques, indicating that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on IoT applications such as healthcare and traffic monitoring, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of implementing these DL-based approaches in practical MCS systems, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
